[[File:Antoon Verschoot.JPG|thumb|Antoon Verschoot]] '''Antoon Verschoot''', {{post-nominals|MBE|size=100%}}, [[Order of the Crown (Belgium)]] ([[Ypres]], 19 June 1925 - 1 February 2017) was a Belgian [[firefighter]] and [[bugler]] who played the [[last post]] at the [[Menin Gate]] for many years.<ref>{{cite web|title=Former bugler Antoon Verschoot dies at the age of 91|url=http://www.lastpost.be/en/news/131/former-bugler-antoon-verschoot-dies-at-the-age-of-91|publisher=Last Post Association|accessdate=11 April 2017}}</ref>
==Background== On 12 December 2015, Antoon Verschoot played his last "Last Post" at the Menin Gate,<ref>Menin Gate</ref> after 65 years with the Ypres/Ieper fire brigade, which he joined in 1950. He became a bugler for the Last Post Association<ref>Last Post Association</ref> in 1954 making him the oldest and longest serving bugler with the Association. It is estimated that Verschoot played at The Gate over 15,000 times.<ref>{{cite web|title=Retirement|url=https://www.facebook.com/lastpostieper/|website=Last Post Association|accessdate=1 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=The last Last Post of Antoon Verschoot|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=11562666|accessdate=16 December 2015|publisher=New Zealand Herold|date=2 January 2016}}</ref>
