==Most prominent summits==
{{GeoGroup|section=Most prominent summits}}
Of the most prominent summits of Nevada, [[Mount Charleston|Charleston Peak]] and [[Wheeler Peak (Nevada)|Wheeler Peak]] exceed {{convert|2000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic prominence, eight peaks are ultra-prominent summits with more than {{convert|1500|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic prominence, and the following 52 peaks exceed {{convert|1400|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}.
{{clear}}
